FBIS4-58623 "drnes088_r_94003" FBIS-NES-94-088 Daily Report 5 May 1994 India Iranian Envoy Summoned About Remarks on Kashmir Iranian Envoy Summoned About Remarks on Kashmir BK0505131194 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1230 GMT 5 May 94 BK0505131194 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] India has conveyed its disappointment at the Iranian ambassador's statement after his visit to Jammu and Kashmir. The ambassador, Mr. (Reza Sheikh Akhtar), was summoned to the foreign office in New Delhi to convey India's reaction to his statement. An External Affairs Ministry spokesman said in New Delhi that it was not the Jammu and Kashmir government which put any hurdle but the Hurriyat Conference leaders themselves in arranging a meeting with the Iranian ambassador. He said the European troika ambassadors and others, who visited the state, appreciated India's transparent policy on Kashmir and their reaction was positive.
